        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 2:31PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 230 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles southwest of Ironside, or 40 miles southeast of John Day,
moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of SE GRANT COUNTY.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
